  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>Cluster Bundle Endpoints (execute commands on the cluster master)</title>
      <html>
       <p>
          <b>Pushes a bundle:</b>
        </p>
       <p>curl -k -u admin:pass https://host:mPort/services/cluster/master/control/default/apply -X POST</p>
       <p>
          <b>Cancels and resets the bundle push operation. Use this endpoint when the cluster master does not receive a validation response from the cluster peer due to an error:</b>
        </p>
       <p>curl -k -u admin:pass https://host:mPort/services/cluster/master/control/default/cancel_bundle_push -X POST</p>
       <p>
          <b>Roll a bundle back to the previously active bundle:</b>
        </p>
       <p>curl -k -u admin:pass https://host:mPort/services/cluster/master/control/default/rollback -X POST</p>
       <p>
          <b>Tests if the bundle in etc/master-apps passes validation. Optionally, tests if the bundle will trigger an indexer restart:</b>
        </p>
       <p>curl -k -u admin:pass https://host:mPort/services/cluster/master/control/default/validate_bundle -d check-restart=true -X POST</p>
       
       <p>
          <b>example:</b>
        </p>
        <p>curl -k -u admin:pass https://127.0.0.1:8089/services/cluster/master/control/default/cancel_bundle_push -X POST</p>
        <br/>
        
        <p>
          <b>Use the CLI to show cluster bundle status:</b>
        </p>
         <p>./splunk show cluster-bundle-status</p>
        <p>
          <b>Use the CLI to validate the bundle and check restart:</b>
        </p>
        <p>./splunk validate cluster-bundle --check-restart</p>
        <p>
          <b>Use the CLI to apply the bundle to the peers</b>
        </p>
        <p>./splunk apply cluster-bundle</p>
       
        <p>
          <b>index cluster bundle operation flow on peer:</b>
        </p>
        <p>1.) Download the bundle from cluster master</p>
        <p>2.) Untar and validate the bundle</p>
        <p>3.) Inform validation status to cluster master</p>
        <p>4.) If master tells to apply</p>
        <p>5.) Apply the bundle</p>
        <p>6.) Inform master if rolling restart is necessary for bundle application</p>
        
        
        
        
        
        <br/>
         <p>
          <a href="https://docs.splunk.com/Documentation/Splunk/7.2.6/Indexer/Configurationbundleissues" target="_blank" class="external">Learn More</a>
        </p>
        
      </html>
